description:
An implementation of the Scheme programming language.

Chez Scheme is an implementation of a superset of the Scheme programming language as described by The Revised6 Report on the Algorithmic Language Scheme (R6RS). It includes a native-code compiler as well as an interpreter and can interface with code written in C through its foreign function interface.
Updates and bug fixes since October 16, 2023.
